.TH QLIP 1 "2025" "qlip 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
qlip \- lightweight screenshot utility
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B qlip
[\fB\-a\fR|\fB\-p\fR|\fB\-w\fR] [\fB\-m\fR [\fINUMBERS\fR]] [\fB\-c\fR] [\fB\-s\fR]
.br
.B qlip gui
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B qlip
captures screenshots on X11 and Wayland Linux desktops. It supports
full-screen, region-select, and per-window capture across multiple monitors.
The display server is auto-detected at runtime.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-a
Capture the entire screen (all connected monitors). Each monitor is saved
as a separate file.
.TP
.B \-a \-m
Capture only the monitor containing the currently active window.
.TP
.B \-a \-m \fINUMBERS\fR
Capture only the specified monitors. Numbers are concatenated digits,
e.g. \fB\-m 13\fR captures monitors 1 and 3.
.TP
.B \-p
Interactively select a rectangular region to capture.
.TP
.B \-w
Open a window-selection dialog and capture the chosen window.
.TP
.B \-w \-c
Capture the currently active/focused window without prompting.
.TP
.B \-s
Prompt for a save directory (one-time; does not change the default).
.TP
.B gui
Open the graphical settings and capture interface.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/qlip/config.json
User configuration (save directory, filetype, filename template).
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.SS X11
maim, slop, xdotool, xrandr, python3-tkinter. Optional: wmctrl.
.SS Wayland
grim, slurp, python3-tkinter. One of: swaymsg (sway), hyprctl (Hyprland),
or wlr-randr (generic wlroots).
.SH AUTHOR
qlip contributors.
